<h2 id="apostrophes-and-quotation-marks">Apostrophes and Quotation Marks</h2>

<p>Use the typographic characters (also called smart quotes) for apostrophes and quotation marks.</p>

<p>Note that in Firefox for desktop and Firefox for Android in en-US this rule is enforced programmatically so a developer’s code will be backed out if a text string contains the straight apostrophe or quote.</p>

<h2 id="commas">Commas</h2>

<p>In the product, use serial commas (also called Oxford commas).</p>

<div class="grid-2">
<div>
    <p class="img">The success of the internet as a public resource depends upon interoperability, innovation, and decentralized participation worldwide.</p>

